# Survey the periphery

## Step

Inventory and lightly grade every memory store OUTSIDE the core loop: Claude's
file-based auto-memory (`~/.claude/projects/-Users-joel/memory/` — note
Joel's 2026-07-16 instruction that durable operator memory belongs in the
Brain, not there), the rhizome/briefing claims system (find it — session
starts show "Rhizomatic briefing" with topics/claims/contested/distrusted),
the wiki's `memory-pulse.json` surface (what feeds it, who reads it),
Typesense + pdf-brain (book index on flagg, full text on the NAS), voice
recall (`joelclaw/infra/voice-agent/voice_recall.py`), the system-bus
memory-friction suites (the ~23 chronically failing MEM/FRIC tests — what
are they supposed to protect?), and anything else found that persists
knowledge for Joel or agents (session summaries, observation stores, etc.).
For each: what it stores, who writes it, who reads it, whether it overlaps or
contradicts the core loop, and a verdict (working / wobbly / gap) with one
receipt each. Produce an asset `periphery-survey.svx`. Depth: map-and-grade,
not deep-dive — flag anything that deserves its own effort. Read-only.

## Result (2026-07-17)

Asset: [Memory system periphery survey](./periphery-survey.svx)

- Claude auto-memory — `wobbly`
- Rhizomatic / Chorus claims — `wobbly`
- Wiki memory pulse — `working`
- Typesense + PDF Brain — `working`
- Voice work recall — `working`
- MEM / FRIC acceptance suites — `wobbly`
- Typesense `memory_observations` — `gap`
- Legacy curated `~/.joelclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md` — `gap`
- Run/session archive and capture state — `wobbly`
- Voice transcript archive — `working`
- Vault system log + PDS mirror — `gap`

The asset includes one live receipt per verdict and six follow-up efforts. The
largest immediate operational risk is the Run capture outbox: 14,798 files,
71.38 GB, and current 404 writes mixed with successful captures.
